"""VESPER Graphiti Integration — singleton client + sync wrappers.

VESPER-14: Replaces Mem0 + pgvector with Graphiti + FalkorDB.
Provides get_graphiti_client(), search_memories(), add_episode() for use
by vesper_context.py and updater.py.

VESPER-22: Added search_memories_structured() with COMBINED_HYBRID_SEARCH_RRF.
Updated search_memories() to use 4-channel hybrid search.

VESPER-23: Added memory decay + reinforcement scoring.
- strength attribute incremented on retrieved entity nodes (+0.1, capped 2.0)
- decay_all_entities() multiplies all Entity strengths by 0.99 (daily)
- log_weak_entities() identifies entities with strength < 0.3
- APScheduler wires daily decay at startup (graceful fallback if not installed)

VESPER-27: Fixed _run_async using a persistent dedicated event loop.
Previous approach (asyncio.run() per call) created a new loop each time,
breaking FalkorDB connections bound to the init loop. Previous attempt
(run_coroutine_threadsafe on running loop) caused deadlock when called
from the event loop thread (LangGraph --allow-blocking mode).

Fix: one persistent loop in a daemon thread; all Graphiti coroutines are
scheduled on it via run_coroutine_threadsafe from any calling thread.
No deadlock, no stale loops.

VESPER-36: Fixed _run_cypher — FalkorDriver has no .query() attribute.
Use driver.execute_query(cypher, **params) instead.
"""
